# Project 3 — Cost Optimization Report

**Status:** ⏳ Coming soon  
**Estimated AWS cost:** $0 (free tier — analysis only)  
**Time to complete:** ~2 hours  

---

## Business Problem

Cloud costs are one of the top concerns for every AWS customer. Without active management, bills grow through idle resources, over-provisioned instances, and unused services. A Solutions Architect and Technical Account Manager both need to identify waste, quantify savings, and present recommendations in business terms — not just technical ones.

This project simulates a real cost review engagement, producing a written report with findings and recommendations as if presenting to a business stakeholder.

---

## Tools Used

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| AWS Budgets | Set spending thresholds and email alerts |
| Cost Explorer | Visualize spending by service, region, and time period |
| Trusted Advisor | Automated recommendations across cost, security, and performance |
| CloudTrail | Audit log — who did what and when |

---

## Report Structure

### 1. Executive Summary
*(one paragraph — what was reviewed, what was found, what the recommendation is)*

### 2. Current Spend Analysis
*(Cost Explorer screenshots and observations)*

### 3. Trusted Advisor Findings
*(list each finding, its severity, and the recommended action)*

### 4. Budget and Alert Configuration
*(screenshot of configured budget and alert thresholds)*

### 5. Recommendations
*(prioritized list with estimated savings or risk reduction for each)*

### 6. Conclusion
*(what was implemented, what remains as future work)*

